``` javascript
editor.edit(function (textEditorEdit) {
    return textEditorEdit.insert(position, "new silently inserted text");
}, true); // <-- silent == true
```

This would make my life easier for my remote pair programming app: [vscode-motepair](https://github.com/drew-wallace/vscode-motepair)

From verifying #10446
(on Linux, 1.5.0-insider, Commit d2c04e3789757413ae1ebfda9d88896686b6d006)

```
let input = vscode.Uri.file("/home/aeschli/workspaces/samples/docker/gooo/kl").toString();

console.log("root: " + workspace.rootPath);
console.log("input: " + input);
console.log("output: " + workspace.asRelativePath(input));
```

Output:

root: /home/aeschli/workspaces/samples/docker
input: file:///home/aeschli/workspaces/samples/docker/gooo/kl
output: file:///home/aeschli/workspaces/samples/docker/gooo/kl

I would have expected `gooo/kl`

From verifying #10446
(on Linux, 1.5.0-insider, Commit d2c04e3789757413ae1ebfda9d88896686b6d006)

```
let input = "/home/aeschli/frr/samples/docker";

console.log("root: " + workspace.rootPath);
